WEBVTT

00:02.790 --> 00:04.290
Previously on
"A Million Little Things"...

00:04.290 --> 00:05.710
This stay-at-home dad was once
the lead singer in a band

00:05.710 --> 00:07.000
who opened up
for Kings of Leon --

00:07.000 --> 00:08.250
All: Right over there.

00:08.250 --> 00:09.790
Of course,
that was a decade ago.

00:09.790 --> 00:11.330
I cannot be your therapist.
I can refer you --

00:11.330 --> 00:12.710
When Gary called
to tell me about Jon,

00:12.710 --> 00:14.290
I had a mouthful
of pills.

00:14.290 --> 00:17.500
I-I don't have the courage to
talk to anyone else about it.

00:17.500 --> 00:19.670
Friday at 1:00.
It's my lunch hour.

00:19.670 --> 00:22.250
I will have lunch with you
as a friend.

00:22.250 --> 00:23.330
Thank you.

00:23.330 --> 00:24.500
Eddie: And where
did you meet this one?

00:24.500 --> 00:26.120
10 bucks says
his breast cancer support group,

00:26.120 --> 00:27.790
and if I'm right,
you're gross.

00:27.790 --> 00:29.250
And you're
10 bucks richer.

00:30.670 --> 00:31.540
[ Groans ]

00:31.540 --> 00:32.670
What?

00:32.670 --> 00:33.790
It's just, uh...

00:35.960 --> 00:36.920
Gary: Who was that?

00:36.920 --> 00:38.290
Someone from my past.

00:38.290 --> 00:39.830
You haven't
told me anything.

00:39.830 --> 00:40.880
What are you so scared of?

00:40.880 --> 00:42.540
This is just
supposed to be fun.

00:42.540 --> 00:44.040
Well, right now,
this is not fun,

00:44.040 --> 00:45.380
so maybe come back
when it is.

00:45.380 --> 00:47.000
Are you having an affair?

00:47.000 --> 00:48.670
When you and Delilah
were having sex.

00:48.670 --> 00:49.960
Who else knows?

00:49.960 --> 00:51.330
No one knows.

00:53.290 --> 00:55.170
Eddie:
Katherine found out about us.

00:55.170 --> 00:56.670
Gary and Rome know, too.

00:56.670 --> 00:58.170
How could you?

01:02.380 --> 01:06.040
♪ Ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh ♪
[ Laughter ]

01:06.040 --> 01:09.500
[ Indistinct conversations ]

01:09.500 --> 01:13.290
♪ 24-hour sun,
and we got full of dark ♪

01:13.290 --> 01:15.420
If I buy you another pepper mill
that looks just like that...

01:15.420 --> 01:20.330
♪ We can hide away our problems
till the winter starts ♪

01:20.330 --> 01:23.420
[ Indistinct conversations ]

01:23.420 --> 01:25.920
♪ We pull our walls
and we build them up again ♪
Andiamo.
Jon, thank you.

01:25.920 --> 01:27.540
Pizza is served.

01:27.540 --> 01:28.540
Woman: Yes!

01:28.540 --> 01:29.750
I mean, honestly.

01:29.750 --> 01:31.580
♪ We don't think
they come between us ♪

01:31.580 --> 01:33.210
♪ But we're doing it again ♪

01:33.210 --> 01:36.620
[ Indistinct conversations ]

01:36.620 --> 01:38.040
Len.
Lenny: Hmm.

01:38.040 --> 01:39.420
♪ Yeah, we're doing it again ♪

01:39.420 --> 01:41.040
How's your dad doing?

01:41.040 --> 01:43.170
Didn't sleep great,
so his memory's not good.

01:43.170 --> 01:46.580
Sitting right here...
with an empty glass in my hand.

01:46.580 --> 01:48.170
Well, on the plus side,

01:48.170 --> 01:49.880
he doesn't remember
he's a pain in the ass.

01:51.000 --> 01:54.000
Here ya go, Len.
Thank you.

01:54.000 --> 01:57.000
And I'm not
a pain in the ass.

01:57.000 --> 01:59.170
Hearing's great,
by the way.

01:59.170 --> 02:00.880
Hmm.

02:00.880 --> 02:04.580
Oh, Soph,
you're just in time.

02:04.580 --> 02:07.500
Len, tell your granddaughter
about how I met her mom.

02:07.500 --> 02:09.620
I know what you're doing.
You're quizzing me.

02:09.620 --> 02:11.250
Oh, I am not.

02:11.250 --> 02:13.040
I just like reliving the moment
that I met your daughter.

02:13.040 --> 02:14.460
[ Sighs ]
Can we not?

02:14.460 --> 02:16.120
I've heard this story
a thousand times.

02:16.120 --> 02:17.540
Can I just go
hang with my friends?

02:17.540 --> 02:19.750
No, no, no, no, no, no.
You know the rule.

02:19.750 --> 02:21.380
Friday nights,
we eat at home,

02:21.380 --> 02:23.170
but everybody's invited
to pizza night.

02:23.170 --> 02:25.170
And make them
hear the story?

02:25.170 --> 02:26.460
Yeah, then they won't be
my friends.

02:26.460 --> 02:29.040
It all started
in an airport.

02:29.040 --> 02:30.040
[ Scoffs ] Oh, God.

02:30.040 --> 02:32.040
There we go!
Oh, God.

02:32.040 --> 02:35.830
He was on his way to L.A., and
she was on her way to France.

02:35.830 --> 02:37.750
Okay, can we just eat?

02:37.750 --> 02:40.540
Hey, if we didn't meet at
the airport, you wouldn't exist.

02:40.540 --> 02:45.460
That's right.
Everything happens for a reason.

02:45.460 --> 02:48.880
♪ Yeah, we're doing it again ♪

02:48.880 --> 02:53.080
♪ Will we ever find a home
out there? ♪

02:53.080 --> 02:56.670
♪ Yeah, we're doing it again ♪

02:56.670 --> 03:11.540
♪ Will we ever find a home
out there? ♪

03:11.540 --> 03:14.290
[ Door opens, closes ]

03:14.290 --> 03:17.750
Typically, a regional recurrence
after a mastectomy is --

03:17.750 --> 03:19.000
well,
it can be a forerunner

03:19.000 --> 03:22.790
for simultaneous
or subsequent metastases.

03:22.790 --> 03:24.620
I bet you say that
to all the girls.

03:26.620 --> 03:28.170
Given that your cancer is now
in your lymph nodes,

03:28.170 --> 03:30.120
we need to move swiftly.

03:30.120 --> 03:34.250
First surgery, then systemic
chemotherapy and radiation.

03:34.250 --> 03:36.040
I've laid out
your treatment plan in here.

03:39.500 --> 03:41.460
You understand
that you have cancer

03:41.460 --> 03:43.620
regardless of whether or not
you take this, right?

03:43.620 --> 03:45.080
[ Chuckles ] Yeah.

03:46.920 --> 03:50.120
Um...

03:50.120 --> 03:54.960
i-if I do nothing,
no treatment,

03:54.960 --> 03:57.880
how long do I have
before it gets bad?

03:57.880 --> 03:59.790
Best guess --

03:59.790 --> 04:02.040
three to six months before
your symptoms progress.

04:02.040 --> 04:04.620
♪♪

04:04.620 --> 04:08.380
And after that...
how long?

04:08.380 --> 04:10.420
If you do
absolutely nothing?

04:12.620 --> 04:14.790
You won't live
beyond a year.

04:14.790 --> 04:21.620
♪♪

04:21.620 --> 04:23.250
[ Imitates karate moves,
bones cracking ]

04:23.250 --> 04:25.790
Ah! I just broke your nose
in nine places!

04:25.790 --> 04:28.040
You may stop, but you will never
smell the roses.

04:28.040 --> 04:29.330
[ Both grunting ]

04:29.330 --> 04:31.330
Just broke your tibia.

04:31.330 --> 04:32.880
It's ankle socks
from here on out.

04:32.880 --> 04:35.210
[ Imitates karate moves ]

04:35.210 --> 04:38.380
Ah! I just shattered
your stevia!

04:38.380 --> 04:40.120
Isn't that
an artificial sweetener?

04:40.120 --> 04:41.580
What do you know?
You're 12.

04:41.580 --> 04:43.920
Hey. Hey, hey. You ready to go
to the restaurant?

04:43.920 --> 04:46.500
No, I can't go.
I can't go.

04:46.500 --> 04:48.710
Kids are off from school.
I think Danny has a fever.

04:48.710 --> 04:50.120
I shouldn't leave him alone
with Sophie.

04:51.710 --> 04:53.290
I'm not sick.

04:53.290 --> 04:55.790
D, we discussed this.
Contractor starts Monday.

04:55.790 --> 04:57.460
Regina's finalizing
the layout today.

04:57.460 --> 04:59.540
You're the designer,
so you should be there.

04:59.540 --> 05:02.290
No, I shouldn't.
[ Sighs ]

05:02.290 --> 05:03.460
Kid, I'm gonna need you
to grab me

05:03.460 --> 05:05.920
a chocolate milk
from the garage fridge.

05:05.920 --> 05:08.380
Get yourself one as well,
but let's be clear.

05:08.380 --> 05:10.330
If there is only one left,
it's mine.

05:10.330 --> 05:11.420
Bye, Daniel.

05:11.420 --> 05:14.290
Goodbye, Gary-san.
[ Door opens ]

05:14.290 --> 05:15.580
You got to stop
avoiding Regina.

05:15.580 --> 05:17.040
It's been a week.
[ Door closes ]

05:17.040 --> 05:19.710
I get it. Your adult playdates
with Eddie -- upsetting.

05:19.710 --> 05:22.420
But she's your best friend,
and you've got to talk to her.

05:22.420 --> 05:25.380
I did. I sent her
a bunch of texts.

05:25.380 --> 05:26.960
She didn't reply.

05:26.960 --> 05:29.420
Okay, if Eddie and I can come
together [chuckles] and talk,

05:29.420 --> 05:32.750
like the evolved humans
that we are,

05:32.750 --> 05:34.250
then you two
definitely can.

05:34.250 --> 05:36.670
You and Eddie got into
a hockey fight

05:36.670 --> 05:38.750
10 feet away from Bobby Orr
and you haven't spoken since.

05:38.750 --> 05:40.460
Okay, but...

05:40.460 --> 05:42.620
I fist-bumped Mr. Orr.

05:42.620 --> 05:45.670
[ Chuckles ]
Actually, I-I bumped
his high five. He -- And --

05:45.670 --> 05:48.420
Then he shook my fist,
and that was awkward.
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

05:48.420 --> 05:51.380
But -- Ooh, I'm sorry.
Got to take this.

05:51.380 --> 05:52.710
Hello?
Rome: Hey.

05:52.710 --> 05:53.830
How's it going
over there?

05:53.830 --> 05:55.750
Uh...
I like chicken.

05:55.750 --> 05:56.750
Oh,
is she right there?

05:56.750 --> 05:58.040
Chicken sounds great.

05:58.040 --> 05:59.420
Well, take a look
at the chicken.

05:59.420 --> 06:01.920
Is she an-- Why am I talking
in code? Is she pissed off?

06:01.920 --> 06:03.830
It's a 12-piece, Colonel.

06:03.830 --> 06:06.290
Well, push through, because
I'm done losing friends, okay?

06:06.290 --> 06:08.500
And once these two kiss and
make up, they'll be thanking us.

06:08.500 --> 06:10.620
There'll be high-fives
and fist bumps all around.

06:10.620 --> 06:12.290
Unless, of course, it's you,
at which point,

06:12.290 --> 06:15.170
they'll be like a combination
of both -- Weird.

06:15.170 --> 06:17.540
Stay strong.
Okay, I gotta go.

06:17.540 --> 06:19.750
So...big day.

06:19.750 --> 06:21.830
Yep.
Big day.

06:21.830 --> 06:24.580
Designing your own restaurant,
second chance at your dream.

06:24.580 --> 06:26.670
It's gonna be even bigger and
better and badder than --
You're doing that thing where
you talk a lot for no reason.

06:26.670 --> 06:27.330
Sorry.

06:29.330 --> 06:30.580
Speaking
of second chances...

06:30.580 --> 06:32.460
We talked about this.

06:32.460 --> 06:36.330
I know, but she's
your business partner,

06:36.330 --> 06:38.670
not to mention
your best friend.

06:38.670 --> 06:40.460
Jon left that restaurant
to the both of you.

06:40.460 --> 06:42.380
Yeah, well,
I am guessing he did that

06:42.380 --> 06:44.080
before she slept
with his best friend.

06:45.420 --> 06:51.960
♪♪

06:51.960 --> 06:53.620
Sorry.
Gotta get to work.

06:53.620 --> 07:02.210
♪♪

07:11.880 --> 07:13.750
You might as well wipe
the counter with E. coli.

07:13.750 --> 07:16.170
[ Water running ]

07:19.250 --> 07:21.120
Katherine,
what are we doing?

07:21.120 --> 07:23.420
I have a meeting near Theo's
school, so I can do pickup.

07:23.420 --> 07:25.170
That's not what
I'm talking about.

07:25.170 --> 07:28.120
I know, Eddie.
That's as far as I've gotten.

07:30.210 --> 07:32.380
I don't know where we go
from here.

07:32.380 --> 07:34.710
I'm still trying to figure out
how we got here.

07:39.580 --> 07:41.620
I could blame it all
on you and Delilah, but...

07:44.790 --> 07:47.960
...the truth is, we were broken
long before that.

07:47.960 --> 07:51.540
[ "Be My Katie" plays ]

07:51.540 --> 07:55.170
♪ Be my, be my Katie ♪

07:55.170 --> 07:57.920
♪ Oh-oh, oh-oh, ooh-oh, oh ♪

07:57.920 --> 08:04.000
♪ Be my Katie tonight ♪

08:04.000 --> 08:07.330
♪♪

08:07.330 --> 08:08.330
♪ Tonight ♪

08:08.330 --> 08:09.710
Whoo!

08:09.710 --> 08:14.830
♪♪

08:14.830 --> 08:17.830
Thank you, Boston!
We're the Red Ferns!

08:17.830 --> 08:20.500
We love you! Whoo!

08:20.500 --> 08:22.580
-Whoa!
-Whoo!

08:22.580 --> 08:24.120
Awesome!

08:24.120 --> 08:26.580
Amazing! Mwah!
[ Laughs ]

08:26.580 --> 08:28.170
-My God!
-Whoo.

08:28.170 --> 08:30.080
Congratulations, man!
Thank you! Thank you!

08:30.080 --> 08:31.290
You killed it!

08:31.290 --> 08:33.290
They are screaming
for you, man!

08:33.290 --> 08:35.080
Also, this!

08:35.080 --> 08:37.000
I gave a Russian chick
a backstage pass.

08:37.000 --> 08:38.210
Not a euphemism.

08:38.210 --> 08:41.170
And if she asks,
I am your drummer.

08:41.170 --> 08:43.790
-Okay. But do me a favor.
-Yeah?

08:43.790 --> 08:46.540
Don't be my drummer
until after the encore.

08:46.540 --> 08:47.880
[ Laughter ]
Whoo!

08:47.880 --> 08:49.120
♪♪

08:49.120 --> 08:51.620
Whoo! Baby.

08:51.620 --> 08:53.330
That last one
was for you.

08:53.330 --> 08:55.960
And this next one's gonna be
for our unborn child,

08:55.960 --> 08:57.670
little baby Milton.

08:57.670 --> 08:59.080
[ Laughs ]

08:59.080 --> 09:00.420
I know he was
your favorite uncle.

09:00.420 --> 09:02.120
We're talking about
that name.
Ah!

09:02.120 --> 09:03.580
Give it to us!

09:03.580 --> 09:05.080
[ Cheers and applause ]
Thank you, Boston!

09:07.210 --> 09:09.000
Theo: Can I have pancakes?

09:09.000 --> 09:10.540
-Hey!
-Hey!

09:10.540 --> 09:11.960
Little man!
Hey.

09:11.960 --> 09:13.620
Yes,
you can have pancakes.

09:13.620 --> 09:15.330
Daddy makes
the best pancakes.

09:15.330 --> 09:16.120
I do.

09:17.880 --> 09:19.080
[ Door closes ]

09:19.080 --> 09:20.750
-Hello?
-Ashley.

09:20.750 --> 09:21.670
Hi.
Thank you.

09:21.670 --> 09:23.210
Oh.

09:23.210 --> 09:25.210
Ah, more mail
from the office,

09:25.210 --> 09:26.790
the bank statements
that you asked for,

09:26.790 --> 09:29.210
and, uh,
Jon's dry-cleaning.

09:29.210 --> 09:31.040
Oh, thank God.
Just in time.

09:31.040 --> 09:32.290
Nice.

09:32.290 --> 09:33.830
Yeah, I found the ticket
in my car.

09:33.830 --> 09:36.210
It just felt weird
not picking it up.

09:36.210 --> 09:39.000
Maybe we could give these
to Goodwill.

09:39.000 --> 09:40.500
I think Jon
would like that.

09:40.500 --> 09:42.250
No.

09:42.250 --> 09:43.830
We're not giving
Dad's stuff away.

09:43.830 --> 09:48.170
♪♪

09:48.170 --> 09:51.210
Well, this is super fun,
but the restaurant awaits.

09:51.210 --> 09:53.290
Time to stop stalling,
D.

09:53.290 --> 09:54.580
I can't -- I can't go.

09:54.580 --> 09:57.290
He really did feel warm
this morning.

09:57.290 --> 09:59.670
He feels warm because he's been
fake karate-chopping me

09:59.670 --> 10:01.250
for the last 20 minutes.

10:01.250 --> 10:03.750
If you have to go somewhere,
I can look after Danny.

10:03.750 --> 10:06.750
Ashley here can look after Danny
and his non-fever.

10:06.750 --> 10:09.210
So will you please grab
your lady things?

10:10.620 --> 10:12.330
Thanks, Ashley.

10:12.330 --> 10:14.000
We'll be back
this afternoon.

10:14.000 --> 10:16.790
Hey, what's the plan
for dinner tonight?

10:16.790 --> 10:18.670
It's Friday.

10:18.670 --> 10:21.000
Pizza night?

10:21.000 --> 10:23.710
I thought we could try
the Thai place on Beacon,

10:23.710 --> 10:25.210
do something new.

10:25.210 --> 10:27.920
I love you, guys.
Be good.

10:27.920 --> 10:31.670
♪♪

10:31.670 --> 10:33.500
Does Regina even know
I'm coming?

10:33.500 --> 10:34.670
Of course she does.

10:34.670 --> 10:36.120
And she's in a very good place
about it.

10:37.500 --> 10:40.540
Whoa! J-Just...

10:40.540 --> 10:42.880
wanted to confirm that
we're definitely not, like,

10:42.880 --> 10:44.250
working through
anything here?

10:44.250 --> 10:45.170
I'm fine.

10:47.750 --> 10:50.750
In fact, I'm great, because
now I can tell the contractor

10:50.750 --> 10:52.960
that there is brick
behind this wall.

10:52.960 --> 10:54.170
That is great news.

10:54.170 --> 10:56.580
So, listen, funny story.

10:56.580 --> 10:59.830
I may have told Gary that we
were stopping by this morning,

10:59.830 --> 11:02.420
and he
may have told Delilah...

11:02.420 --> 11:05.790
and I think
they might come by.

11:05.790 --> 11:07.750
Wait. You think
they might come by?

11:07.750 --> 11:10.080
[ Car alarm chirps ]

11:10.080 --> 11:11.710
That's them.
Babe, you didn't.

11:11.710 --> 11:14.830
I know you're upset, but I also
know that you are hurting.

11:14.830 --> 11:16.880
Talk to her.

11:16.880 --> 11:19.380
Okay, well, did it ever occur
to you that I'm avoiding her

11:19.380 --> 11:22.000
because maybe I might
say something that
I can't take back?

11:22.000 --> 11:24.000
[ Door opens ]

11:24.000 --> 11:29.380
♪♪

11:29.380 --> 11:30.540
[ Door closes ]

11:30.540 --> 11:37.500
♪♪

11:37.500 --> 11:44.290
♪♪

11:44.290 --> 11:45.790
Do you want to start
by marking the walls

11:45.790 --> 11:47.960
that we want to come down?

11:47.960 --> 11:49.120
Sounds good.

11:51.290 --> 11:53.580
We could knock down the wall
to the kitchen

11:53.580 --> 11:56.380
and, uh,
make it open concept?

11:56.380 --> 11:58.540
Sure.

11:58.540 --> 12:01.380
Or not.
Or not.

12:01.380 --> 12:03.460
Can you believe this?

12:03.460 --> 12:05.580
You reached out
to Eddie yet?
No.

12:05.580 --> 12:07.120
You want
to talk about it?
No.

12:07.120 --> 12:08.420
Yeah, I can believe this.

12:08.420 --> 12:10.250
He broke bro code.
It's different.

12:10.250 --> 12:12.830
This is ridiculous.
You won't even look at me.

12:15.500 --> 12:18.580
I know you're angry.

12:18.580 --> 12:21.250
What I did, what we did
was wrong, but...

12:23.750 --> 12:26.420
...there's just -- there's --
there's things about my marriage

12:26.420 --> 12:27.330
that you didn't know.

12:29.790 --> 12:32.330
Jon was working all the time,
but even when he was home,

12:32.330 --> 12:35.040
he wasn't --
he wasn't there,

12:35.040 --> 12:38.460
and he was really distant
for the last two years.

12:41.790 --> 12:44.170
I felt invisible,
and Eddie saw me.

12:49.540 --> 12:50.830
[ Scoffs ]

12:50.830 --> 12:52.540
Okay, I should've told you.
I'm sorry.

12:52.540 --> 12:53.960
That's why you're mad?

12:53.960 --> 12:55.500
I'm mad because
if you had told me,

12:55.500 --> 12:57.210
then maybe I could've
been there for you.

12:59.290 --> 13:00.960
Maybe I could've
been there for Jon.

13:01.960 --> 13:03.880
But now he's gone.

13:06.920 --> 13:08.080
Because of me.

13:10.290 --> 13:12.790
That's good. At least you, um --
you said it.

13:12.790 --> 13:14.540
It's --
[ Scoffs ]

13:14.540 --> 13:17.290
I think this was a mistake.
I-I shouldn't have come.

13:17.290 --> 13:18.460
D.

13:18.460 --> 13:21.710
Uh, you should do the restaurant
without me.

13:21.710 --> 13:23.250
I'm done.

13:25.120 --> 13:27.120
[ Door opens ]
[ Sighs ]

13:29.290 --> 13:31.540
[ Door closes ]

13:31.540 --> 13:34.750
Is this when we get the
fist bumps and the high-fives?

13:39.170 --> 13:40.500
Dad, all I'm saying is
that while I'm driving,

13:40.500 --> 13:41.580
you need to not
touch the wheel.

13:41.580 --> 13:43.380
And all I'm saying is
you need to commit

13:43.380 --> 13:45.120
to honking the horn more.

13:46.210 --> 13:48.830
Maybe you trust me
to drive myself.

13:48.830 --> 13:50.210
I was
in the neighborhood.

13:52.290 --> 13:53.460
Right, Soph?

13:53.460 --> 13:55.210
Whatever it is,
I take his side.

13:55.210 --> 13:57.170
[ Chuckles ]
Hey, sweetie.

13:57.170 --> 13:58.670
Where is, uh...

13:59.670 --> 14:00.920
The boy.

14:00.920 --> 14:02.420
Um...
Danny.

14:02.420 --> 14:05.500
Danny!
Yes, I know my grandson's name!

14:05.500 --> 14:11.880
♪♪

14:11.880 --> 14:14.580
Sorry. I'm just...

14:14.580 --> 14:15.920
I'm sorry.

14:15.920 --> 14:19.460
♪♪

14:19.460 --> 14:22.420
It's okay.
He's upstairs.

14:22.420 --> 14:25.330
Danny's upstairs,
and he's excited to see you.

14:25.330 --> 14:34.580
♪♪

14:34.580 --> 14:36.080
Who put this back up?

14:36.080 --> 14:37.670
I did.

14:37.670 --> 14:38.960
You're so worried
about your dad.

14:38.960 --> 14:40.210
How about you worry
about mine?

14:40.210 --> 14:41.960
What does that mean?

14:41.960 --> 14:43.880
Oh, come on, Mom.

14:43.880 --> 14:45.710
We all see it.

14:45.710 --> 14:47.920
Every day, you push away
more and more of him.

14:47.920 --> 14:50.380
God, I mean,
for the past two Fridays,

14:50.380 --> 14:52.620
there's been some excuse
not to do pizza night --

14:52.620 --> 14:54.830
Dad's night.

14:54.830 --> 14:57.540
I used to hate Fridays.

14:57.540 --> 14:58.790
But now...

15:00.420 --> 15:02.880
...all I want is to be bored
by Grandpa's stories

15:02.880 --> 15:05.000
while waiting
for Dad's pizza.

15:05.000 --> 15:07.960
I want to remember him.

15:07.960 --> 15:09.500
Why -- Why don't you?

15:09.500 --> 15:12.170
I... [ Sighs ]

15:12.170 --> 15:13.290
I was...

15:15.210 --> 15:17.210
I was just trying
to protect you.

15:19.120 --> 15:21.960
Yeah, well, doesn't feel
like you're protecting us.

15:21.960 --> 15:24.620
It feels like
you're erasing him.

15:24.620 --> 15:30.620
♪♪

15:30.620 --> 15:32.380
Oh.

15:32.380 --> 15:36.500
♪♪

15:36.500 --> 15:39.250
[ Indistinct conversations ]

15:39.250 --> 15:41.000
[ Sighs ]

15:54.790 --> 15:56.170
Hey, stranger.

15:56.170 --> 15:58.420
Hi.

15:58.420 --> 16:00.040
You okay?

16:00.040 --> 16:02.120
Yeah, yeah, I'm fine.

16:03.710 --> 16:07.210
Admittedly, my birthday, uh,
makes me a little crazy,

16:07.210 --> 16:08.670
and also, I don't know
if you heard,

16:08.670 --> 16:11.460
but there's been some
non-consensual wife swapping...

16:11.460 --> 16:13.170
Mm.
...happening in
the friend group.

16:13.170 --> 16:15.790
I heard. I'm sorry.

16:15.790 --> 16:18.500
You sure you're okay?
Mm-hmm.

16:21.330 --> 16:23.710
Um, it's just...

16:26.500 --> 16:27.880
...this morning,
I had to go --

16:27.880 --> 16:29.040
Hey, Gare-Bear.

16:29.040 --> 16:30.710
Rebecca.

16:30.710 --> 16:31.960
Long time.

16:31.960 --> 16:33.080
It's been --
It's been a while.

16:33.080 --> 16:34.670
You look good.

16:34.670 --> 16:36.170
It's been a good,
long while.

16:36.170 --> 16:39.290
Yeah, well, I just got back from
this six-week intense detox.

16:39.290 --> 16:41.750
I mean, you would not believe
the amount of mucoid plaque

16:41.750 --> 16:43.290
that came out of me.
[ Laughs ]
Wow.

16:43.290 --> 16:45.000
Wow.
[ Chuckles ]

16:45.000 --> 16:47.420
That's a lot to process.
Yeah. Yeah, it was.

16:47.420 --> 16:49.670
But, you know, honestly,
I've never felt better.

16:49.670 --> 16:52.000
My insides are
literally glowing.

16:52.000 --> 16:53.250
You should, uh...

16:53.250 --> 16:55.290
you should see them.
Ah-mazing.

16:55.290 --> 16:57.380
[ Chuckles ] Hi, Rebecca.
I'm Maggie.

16:57.380 --> 16:59.120
Hi, Maggie. Welcome.

16:59.120 --> 17:00.420
[ Both chuckle ]

17:00.420 --> 17:01.830
Oh, I wouldn't
if I were you.

17:01.830 --> 17:04.080
Gluten wreaks havoc
on the adrenals.

17:04.080 --> 17:06.210
Oh. Good to know.

17:08.880 --> 17:11.170
Anyway, missed you,
Gare-Bear.

17:11.170 --> 17:14.500
Now that I'm back, we should get
some non-GMO tapas.

17:14.500 --> 17:16.460
[ Clears throat ]
Or, you know, there's always
our spot in the bathroom.

17:16.460 --> 17:21.120
♪♪

17:21.120 --> 17:24.460
Okay. [ Sniffs ]
I can explain.

17:24.460 --> 17:27.120
Explain what, exactly?

17:27.120 --> 17:29.790
That hooking up with survivors
in the church bathroom

17:29.790 --> 17:31.670
is your go-to move?

17:31.670 --> 17:34.040
Don't bother.
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

17:34.040 --> 17:35.790
I knew that
you had intimacy issues,

17:35.790 --> 17:38.790
but sleeping your way through
women with an expiration date

17:38.790 --> 17:39.920
is pathetic.

17:39.920 --> 17:41.500
That's not fair.

17:41.500 --> 17:43.750
Technically, these women
are in remission.

17:45.500 --> 17:46.580
Wow.

17:48.330 --> 17:50.210
Hey, you know what?
You don't get to be upset.

17:50.210 --> 17:52.120
You said we were
just having fun.

17:52.120 --> 17:53.580
You keep asking
for rain checks

17:53.580 --> 17:55.170
when your boyfriend in
the windbreaker shows up.

17:55.170 --> 17:57.170
Ex-boyfriend,
and it's a bomber jacket.

17:57.170 --> 17:59.420
Maggie, you insisted
that there is no us!

17:59.420 --> 18:01.960
You know what, Gary?!
You're right!

18:01.960 --> 18:03.750
I don't have any reason
to be upset,

18:03.750 --> 18:05.500
because I knew exactly
who you were

18:05.500 --> 18:07.880
the moment I fell
for your go-to move.

18:07.880 --> 18:09.420
Let me ask you something.

18:09.420 --> 18:11.460
When you acted like you were
afraid to take your shirt off,

18:11.460 --> 18:13.620
is that just another move
to get inside me?

18:15.710 --> 18:17.000
[ Sighs ]

18:21.330 --> 18:22.790
[ Door closes ]

18:22.790 --> 18:27.120
♪♪

18:32.290 --> 18:33.960
Eddie: Wasn't Tamara the one
with the acai berries

18:33.960 --> 18:36.000
and the vitamin cleanse?

18:36.000 --> 18:38.830
Jon: Yeah, she had me paying
$847,000 a month for juice.
[ Laughs ]

18:38.830 --> 18:40.790
First of all,
it's pronounced ah-sah-ee.

18:40.790 --> 18:42.580
So, that's an embarrassing
moment for Ed.

18:42.580 --> 18:45.670
And secondly, she was
very spirited, okay?

18:45.670 --> 18:47.080
Who wants more sangria?

18:47.080 --> 18:48.210
No, Len.

18:48.210 --> 18:50.040
Eddie doesn't drink,
remember?

18:51.790 --> 18:52.790
Eddie: It's okay.

18:52.790 --> 18:58.330
♪♪

18:58.330 --> 19:00.790
Hey, you didn't have to
embarrass my dad like that.

19:00.790 --> 19:02.710
I was just trying
to keep my friend

19:02.710 --> 19:04.040
with the drinking problem
from drinking.
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

19:04.040 --> 19:06.330
He --
Of course, answer the phone.

19:06.330 --> 19:07.790
Hey.

19:07.790 --> 19:12.170
Everything I do is to
take care of this family.

19:12.170 --> 19:14.040
Tell me
you have good news.

19:14.040 --> 19:16.830
♪♪

19:21.080 --> 19:22.290
[ Knock on door ]

19:22.290 --> 19:24.120
Hi.
I'm heading out.

19:24.120 --> 19:26.040
Thanks for looking after
the kids.

19:26.040 --> 19:28.210
They, um --
They love you.

19:28.210 --> 19:30.080
Well, it's mutual.

19:33.040 --> 19:36.000
You know...

19:36.000 --> 19:39.120
my dad died when I was not
that much older than Sophie.

19:39.120 --> 19:40.620
I'm sorry.

19:40.620 --> 19:42.790
I...I didn't know.

19:42.790 --> 19:45.460
Yeah. I was...

19:45.460 --> 19:47.170
Afterwards,
I was kind of a mess.

19:50.080 --> 19:52.540
Soph's not mad at you.

19:52.540 --> 19:54.710
She's mad at the world.

19:54.710 --> 19:58.330
The thing is,
she should be mad at me.

19:58.330 --> 20:01.210
She's right.

20:01.210 --> 20:05.830
I have been
hiding him away --

20:05.830 --> 20:08.080
everything, everything
that reminds me of him.

20:08.080 --> 20:10.290
I just --
I've been telling myself

20:10.290 --> 20:14.170
that it's because
it's too painful for the kids.

20:14.170 --> 20:16.040
Truth is,
it's too painful for me.

20:18.210 --> 20:20.960
[ Scoffs ] How could I
do this to him?

20:20.960 --> 20:24.710
Come on.
Love is weird.

20:24.710 --> 20:27.750
You know, we don't always get
to choose who and how we love.

20:29.830 --> 20:31.790
Sometimes,
it chooses us.

20:31.790 --> 20:40.710
♪♪

20:40.710 --> 20:49.920
♪♪

20:49.920 --> 20:52.830
[ Elevator bell dings ]
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

20:52.830 --> 20:54.540
[ Sighs ]

20:54.540 --> 20:56.290
Hey, babe,
how you doing?

20:56.290 --> 20:59.540
Oh, you know, compartmentalizing
by way of mushroom tartlets.

20:59.540 --> 21:02.830
Listen, I'm sorry this morning
was such a disaster.

21:02.830 --> 21:04.920
It's my fault, I --
No, it wasn't.

21:04.920 --> 21:07.120
It's mine.

21:07.120 --> 21:08.750
Some things are better
left unsaid.

21:08.750 --> 21:12.880
No, you were just speaking
your truth, and...

21:12.880 --> 21:15.290
Hey, I'm just about to head
into the edit suite,

21:15.290 --> 21:16.790
but I'll be home
in a couple of hours.

21:16.790 --> 21:18.040
Can we talk then?

21:18.040 --> 21:19.790
Sure.
I love you.

21:19.790 --> 21:23.000
I love you, too.
Bye.

21:23.000 --> 21:25.710
So, how is speaking
your truth going?
Yeah, super good.

21:25.710 --> 21:29.120
Cats don't blink
like people do.

21:29.120 --> 21:31.170
Good to know.

21:31.170 --> 21:34.000
So, if you get into
a staring contest with a cat,

21:34.000 --> 21:36.000
you're gonna lose.

21:36.000 --> 21:39.540
Sophie.
Oh, hey.

21:39.540 --> 21:41.170
Um...

21:41.170 --> 21:43.750
I just was wondering
if Eddie had time to jam.

21:43.750 --> 21:45.670
Um...

21:45.670 --> 21:47.750
God, I'm sorry.
I shouldn't have come.

21:47.750 --> 21:49.880
Don't be silly.
You're always welcome here.

21:49.880 --> 21:51.460
You know that.
Come on in.

21:51.460 --> 21:53.210
Theo was just telling me
about cats.

21:53.210 --> 21:54.710
They don't blink
like people do.

21:54.710 --> 22:03.500
♪♪

22:03.500 --> 22:12.710
♪♪

22:12.710 --> 22:19.080
♪♪

22:19.080 --> 22:21.710
[ Band of Horses' "Laredo"
plays ]

22:21.710 --> 22:24.250
♪ Gonna take a trip to Laredo ♪

22:24.250 --> 22:26.830
All right, Sully, come on.
[ Glass taps ]

22:26.830 --> 22:27.880
Let's do this.

22:27.880 --> 22:30.080
Sorry, Eddie,
you're done.

22:32.500 --> 22:34.920
Are you kidding?
No, no, no, Jon,
I got him.

22:34.920 --> 22:36.420
Yeah, yeah, yeah,
I found him.

22:36.420 --> 22:39.000
Okay, tell Katherine
we'll meet you there.

22:39.000 --> 22:40.500
Thanks, Sully.

22:40.500 --> 22:44.330
Did you call him?
Is this what this is?

22:44.330 --> 22:46.750
Sully, you don't call him.
The customer's always right.

22:46.750 --> 22:48.670
Fill me up, man.
Come on.
You're done. Let's go.

22:48.670 --> 22:50.250
Why would I go anywhere
with you, Gary?

22:50.250 --> 22:54.790
Because Katherine's
in labor, okay?

22:54.790 --> 22:56.920
You're gonna be a father.

22:56.920 --> 23:01.250
♪♪

23:04.330 --> 23:06.120
Rome: And I'm sitting here,
listening to these ad execs

23:06.120 --> 23:09.710
tell me that we need to
"feel the thirst."

23:09.710 --> 23:11.750
And all I can think is,
"What am I doing?

23:11.750 --> 23:13.710
The best years of my life have
been spent making people care

23:13.710 --> 23:17.580
about soda, pizza,
and kitty litter."

23:17.580 --> 23:19.250
That's it. That's my life,
and it's killing me.

23:21.710 --> 23:23.960
I didn't mean...

23:23.960 --> 23:24.710
It's just a saying.

23:24.710 --> 23:26.290
Is it?

23:26.290 --> 23:30.250
There's, um, a study they did
a while back about people

23:30.250 --> 23:32.670
who survived jumping off
the Brooklyn Bridge.

23:32.670 --> 23:34.790
Only 1% survived.

23:34.790 --> 23:37.000
But of that 1%,

23:37.000 --> 23:40.750
100% regretted it
the moment they jumped.

23:42.170 --> 23:45.380
One of the survivors that they
interviewed said something

23:45.380 --> 23:50.580
that I have been thinking
about, um...a lot lately,

23:50.580 --> 23:56.040
and she said, "It's not that
I don't want to live.

23:56.040 --> 23:58.750
It's that I don't want
to live like this."

23:58.750 --> 24:02.210
♪♪

24:02.210 --> 24:04.170
Regina's pursuing
her dream.

24:04.170 --> 24:06.750
When are you gonna
pursue yours?

24:06.750 --> 24:09.710
Now's not the time,
you know?

24:09.710 --> 24:11.500
With the new restaurant,

24:11.500 --> 24:14.420
we need that Shasta money now
more than ever.

24:14.420 --> 24:16.920
Isn't that a decision
you should make together?

24:19.330 --> 24:22.330
I mean...last I checked,

24:22.330 --> 24:23.920
you were the one
with the mouthful of pills.

24:30.960 --> 24:33.000
♪ It always seems to be ♪

24:33.000 --> 24:35.920
♪ I've seen that depression ♪

24:35.920 --> 24:38.670
♪ Has really got a hold on you ♪

24:38.670 --> 24:40.080
Eddie?

24:40.080 --> 24:41.710
Damn, it is you.

24:41.710 --> 24:42.580
Sully!

24:42.580 --> 24:46.170
W-Wh--
Man, it's been --

24:46.170 --> 24:48.420
It's been ages, yeah.
[ Chuckles ]

24:48.420 --> 24:50.750
[ Chuckles ] Yo,
what are you doing here?

24:50.750 --> 24:54.750
[ Inhales sharply ]
Well...

24:54.750 --> 24:57.960
I have been thinking about
maybe performing again,

24:57.960 --> 24:59.790
getting back on stage.

24:59.790 --> 25:03.420
Um, I have all these new songs
I've been working on.

25:03.420 --> 25:06.000
I thought you gave
that all up, man.

25:06.000 --> 25:08.620
Yeah, so did I.

25:08.620 --> 25:10.750
Gary:
I'm an actuary, Evelyn.

25:10.750 --> 25:12.710
I do this for a living.

25:12.710 --> 25:14.080
[ Chuckles ] Okay, okay.

25:14.080 --> 25:16.790
How much do you think
his life is worth?

25:16.790 --> 25:19.420
500 gran-- Come on.

25:19.420 --> 25:22.540
Live in the world.
We've done this dance before.

25:22.540 --> 25:25.170
That number is 248K, tops.

25:25.170 --> 25:27.460
He was a 29-year-old barista

25:27.460 --> 25:29.750
living at home
with his parents, okay?

25:29.750 --> 25:32.580
I've got two words for you --
basement, bedroom.

25:32.580 --> 25:34.880
Ksshhhhhh.

25:34.880 --> 25:36.790
That's it. That's what he did
all day long.

25:36.790 --> 25:39.330
Ksshhhhh.

25:39.330 --> 25:42.210
No. I'm not in a mood.

25:42.210 --> 25:45.580
I'm simply telling you
what the chart says.

25:45.580 --> 25:47.620
All right.
Hit me back.

25:52.170 --> 25:54.460
[ Ringing ]

25:54.460 --> 25:55.620
Maggie: Hey, it's Maggie.
Leave me a message.

25:55.620 --> 25:56.330
[ Beep ]

25:58.540 --> 26:00.210
[ Door closes ]

26:00.210 --> 26:02.460
Hey, babe.
How was post?

26:02.460 --> 26:04.040
Good.

26:08.460 --> 26:10.000
Actually...

26:11.330 --> 26:12.540
Actually, it wasn't.

26:12.540 --> 26:14.380
I know that now
is not a good time,

26:14.380 --> 26:16.790
and we need the money more now
than ever with the restaurant,

26:16.790 --> 26:18.670
but I can't.

26:18.670 --> 26:21.000
I can't.
I-I can't do it.

26:21.000 --> 26:23.080
Can't do what?
I hate my job.

26:23.080 --> 26:26.330
I hate it.
I hate myself for doing it.

26:26.330 --> 26:28.000
I hate the people
that I work with.

26:28.000 --> 26:29.790
It's soul-crushing!

26:29.790 --> 26:33.170
I want to quit my job,
and I want to make my movie.

26:38.000 --> 26:40.330
That's what
you should do, then.

26:43.330 --> 26:44.710
What about money, Gina?

26:44.710 --> 26:46.620
Look,
we don't have kids.

26:46.620 --> 26:49.330
We can sell this place,
rent something cheaper.

26:49.330 --> 26:51.460
W-We'll figure it out.

26:55.250 --> 26:57.620
Yeah?
Yeah.

26:57.620 --> 26:59.620
[ Chuckles ]

27:04.330 --> 27:07.830
Look, I didn't realize
it was this bad.

27:07.830 --> 27:10.120
I'm sorry
I didn't see it.

27:10.120 --> 27:12.080
I-I just --

27:12.080 --> 27:13.880
I-I should've seen it.

27:16.540 --> 27:18.460
I should've seen it.

27:23.000 --> 27:25.380
Oh! Hey.
You're Maggie's friend.

27:25.380 --> 27:27.000
I'm Tom.

27:27.000 --> 27:28.420
Gary.
Nice to meet you.

27:28.420 --> 27:30.120
She's, uh --
She's not home.

27:30.120 --> 27:33.210
Grape soda.
How vintage.

27:33.210 --> 27:35.750
Yeah, well, you know
Maggie's obsession
with all things grape.

27:35.750 --> 27:38.330
[ Scoffs ] Totally.
[ Laughs ]

27:38.330 --> 27:40.120
That's actually the first thing
she and I talked about

27:40.120 --> 27:42.380
in our breast cancer
support group.

27:42.380 --> 27:45.080
You have breast cancer,
too?

27:45.080 --> 27:47.080
I did, yeah.
Guys get it.

27:47.080 --> 27:48.170
It's a thing, dude.

27:50.250 --> 27:52.250
Well, then you know what
she's going through.

27:52.250 --> 27:55.040
Um...I-I'm just in town
for a few days.

27:55.040 --> 27:58.580
I thought I'd drop off
a little care package.

27:58.580 --> 28:01.420
And it can't be easy staring
down another round of treatment.

28:01.420 --> 28:04.460
♪♪

28:04.460 --> 28:06.250
Nope.

28:06.250 --> 28:08.620
No, it can't.

28:08.620 --> 28:10.000
I'm gonna leave this inside.

28:10.000 --> 28:11.920
Can you just let her know
that I stopped by?

28:11.920 --> 28:13.710
I sure will.
All right, man.

28:13.710 --> 28:19.540
♪♪

28:27.460 --> 28:29.210
Regina:
You're doing it all wrong.

28:33.290 --> 28:36.330
Pizza night,
or everything else in my life?

28:39.080 --> 28:41.080
I'm sorry, D.

28:45.710 --> 28:49.920
You were hurting and in pain,
and I didn't see it.

28:52.330 --> 28:55.420
And maybe I didn't
want to see it.

28:55.420 --> 28:57.460
You didn't see it
because I didn't let you.

29:00.290 --> 29:03.250
I'm so ashamed, Gina,

29:03.250 --> 29:05.620
so ashamed of
what I've done.

29:07.960 --> 29:11.960
[ Sighs ] I-I can't --
I can't keep pushing him away.

29:11.960 --> 29:13.330
It's just -- It's not
fair to the kids.

29:15.500 --> 29:17.290
[ Sniffles ]

29:17.290 --> 29:20.290
You know what's not fair
to the kids...

29:20.290 --> 29:24.040
is this
store-bought crust.

29:26.330 --> 29:29.330
If we're gonna do pizza night,
we're gonna do it right.

29:29.330 --> 29:36.080
♪♪

29:42.540 --> 29:44.750
[ Knock on door ]

29:51.380 --> 29:54.790
Gary, whatever this is,
I am not in the mood for it.

29:54.790 --> 29:56.580
Well, Maggie,
you won't return my calls.

29:56.580 --> 30:00.830
And I want to talk about
the night in the bathroom.

30:00.830 --> 30:02.040
Well, I don't.

30:02.040 --> 30:03.620
Well, you could listen.

30:03.620 --> 30:04.540
Please?

30:06.750 --> 30:07.920
Thank you.

30:09.000 --> 30:11.540
[ Sighs ]

30:11.540 --> 30:14.080
Yes, okay?

30:14.080 --> 30:17.500
The answer is -- Yes, I've been
in that bathroom before.

30:17.500 --> 30:20.210
Yes, I've been with women
in that bathroom before.

30:20.210 --> 30:22.380
Yeah, and this is the part where
you tell me that I'm different?

30:22.380 --> 30:23.920
No.

30:23.920 --> 30:26.040
This is the part where I tell
you that I'm different.

30:31.540 --> 30:34.210
I don't think you are.

30:34.210 --> 30:35.750
I know I'm a-a therapist,

30:35.750 --> 30:40.330
and my whole job is about
helping people change, but...

30:40.330 --> 30:42.120
I don't think you can.

30:43.920 --> 30:45.000
You should go.

30:46.710 --> 30:48.920
[ Door opens ]

30:48.920 --> 30:56.540
♪♪

30:56.540 --> 31:03.960
♪♪

31:03.960 --> 31:11.500
♪♪

31:11.500 --> 31:12.710
[ Door closes ]

31:12.710 --> 31:18.040
♪♪

31:18.040 --> 31:22.920
♪♪

31:22.920 --> 31:24.710
[ Exhales sharply ]

31:24.710 --> 31:33.710
♪♪

31:33.710 --> 31:42.710
♪♪

31:42.710 --> 31:51.750
♪♪

31:55.250 --> 31:57.540
Katherine:
Eddie should be home soon.

32:04.420 --> 32:06.580
I may not be able to jam
with you like Eddie,

32:06.580 --> 32:09.380
but I'm an attorney.

32:09.380 --> 32:10.960
So anything you tell me
could technically fall

32:10.960 --> 32:12.620
under attorney-client
privilege.

32:15.420 --> 32:19.170
I just had a huge fight
with my mom.

32:19.170 --> 32:21.120
You know,
ever since my dad died,

32:21.120 --> 32:25.120
she's been pretending
like everything's normal.

32:25.120 --> 32:28.040
Except it's not normal,
and it never will be.

32:28.040 --> 32:29.330
[ Sighs ]

32:29.330 --> 32:32.210
I know. It's hard.

32:32.210 --> 32:35.540
I can't even imagine what
you are all going through.

32:35.540 --> 32:38.540
Sometimes she'll go into her
bathroom and turn on the shower

32:38.540 --> 32:40.620
so that I won't
hear her crying.

32:40.620 --> 32:44.880
♪♪

32:44.880 --> 32:47.460
It's not easy
being the strong one,

32:47.460 --> 32:49.790
being the responsible one.

32:49.790 --> 32:53.830
But I promise you,

32:53.830 --> 32:56.880
everything your mom does,

32:56.880 --> 32:59.880
she does out of love.

32:59.880 --> 33:01.880
And sometimes putting on
a brave face

33:01.880 --> 33:06.170
and pretending
everything is fine...

33:06.170 --> 33:08.040
that's the hardest job
of all.

33:10.080 --> 33:12.540
Hey.

33:12.540 --> 33:14.380
Hey.

33:14.380 --> 33:17.710
Sophie dropped by
for an impromptu lesson.

33:17.710 --> 33:19.830
Sophie, that is
some dedication.

33:19.830 --> 33:21.620
What do you say
you go set up out back?

33:21.620 --> 33:22.880
Oh, yeah.

33:22.880 --> 33:29.670
♪♪

33:29.670 --> 33:31.080
Thanks, Katherine.

33:31.080 --> 33:32.670
Anytime, Soph.

33:32.670 --> 33:40.120
♪♪

33:40.120 --> 33:42.380
Hey, um...

33:42.380 --> 33:45.120
this morning,
you asked how we got here.

33:47.380 --> 33:50.540
When my life
went to hell...

33:50.540 --> 33:53.540
and I got thrown out
of the band, you stepped up.

33:53.540 --> 33:57.210
You were the strong one
when I couldn't be.

33:57.210 --> 33:59.670
I put you in a situation
you never asked to be in,

33:59.670 --> 34:01.670
and I am so sorry
for that.

34:05.250 --> 34:06.830
Thank you
for saying that.

34:06.830 --> 34:11.540
♪♪

34:11.540 --> 34:12.960
You better go.
Sophie's waiting.

34:12.960 --> 34:17.750
♪♪

34:17.750 --> 34:21.000
[ Exhales deeply ]

34:21.000 --> 34:23.380
That was...

34:23.380 --> 34:25.040
some of our best work.

34:25.040 --> 34:27.170
[ Chuckles ]

34:27.170 --> 34:29.000
Yeah, definitely.

34:31.380 --> 34:32.960
Hmm?

34:32.960 --> 34:34.880
What's going on
in there?

34:37.170 --> 34:38.420
Nothing. Why?

34:38.420 --> 34:40.380
This morning, um,

34:40.380 --> 34:44.500
before you-know-who
came to the support group,

34:44.500 --> 34:47.540
uh, just kind of seemed like
you wanted to tell me something.

34:52.540 --> 34:55.580
Oh, I can't remember.

34:55.580 --> 34:58.040
[ Cellphone vibrates ]
Must not have been important.

34:58.040 --> 35:00.210
You should get that,
Gare-Bear.

35:00.210 --> 35:01.830
You're not calling me
Gare-Bear.

35:01.830 --> 35:03.210
[ Laughs ]
That's not --

35:03.210 --> 35:04.620
That's not
gonna be a thing.

35:04.620 --> 35:05.670
Yes, it is.

35:05.670 --> 35:06.960
[ Sighs ]

35:23.580 --> 35:26.000
♪♪

35:26.000 --> 35:27.540
Tom: What are you doing,
Maggie?

35:27.540 --> 35:29.250
Look at this place.
You haven't even unpacked.

35:29.250 --> 35:30.500
Okay, Tom.

35:30.500 --> 35:33.290
It's because I don't know
if it's worth it.

35:33.290 --> 35:34.830
I mean, how much longer
do I have to live?

35:37.120 --> 35:39.000
I'm scared, okay?

35:40.830 --> 35:43.040
I'm scared to start treatment
all over again.

35:45.500 --> 35:47.460
Give me time.

35:47.460 --> 35:49.920
You don't have time.

35:49.920 --> 35:56.080
♪♪

35:56.080 --> 35:58.420
Gary:
Hey, it's Delilah.

35:58.420 --> 36:01.540
She wants us to come over
for pizza tonight.

36:01.540 --> 36:04.120
Your call.
What should I tell her?

36:04.120 --> 36:13.920
♪♪

36:13.920 --> 36:16.120
Yeah, let's do it.

36:20.790 --> 36:23.380
[ Sighs ] Thank you.

36:23.380 --> 36:24.460
Of course, Sophie.

36:24.460 --> 36:25.920
[ Vehicle door closes ]

36:25.920 --> 36:27.210
[ Imitates explosion ]

36:27.210 --> 36:29.580
You're back just in time
for dinner.

36:29.580 --> 36:31.960
We're having pizza night.

36:31.960 --> 36:34.250
We are?
Mm-hmm.

36:38.540 --> 36:41.250
Thanks for letting me know
where she was

36:41.250 --> 36:43.620
and driving her home.

36:43.620 --> 36:45.000
Of course.

36:49.170 --> 36:51.580
We'll let you
get back to it.

36:51.580 --> 36:53.120
Yeah, we got to head out.

36:53.120 --> 36:54.420
We're just gonna grab
some dinner.

36:54.420 --> 36:55.460
Come on, pal.

36:55.460 --> 36:57.710
How come we can't stay?

36:57.710 --> 36:59.040
I love pizza night.

37:02.460 --> 37:03.960
Oh.

37:03.960 --> 37:06.710
♪♪

37:06.710 --> 37:09.920
Uh, I don't know if that's
such a good idea tonight, bud.

37:09.920 --> 37:12.620
But it's Friday.

37:12.620 --> 37:15.710
Uncle Jon and Aunt D always
have us over on Friday.

37:15.710 --> 37:17.920
Yeah.

37:17.920 --> 37:19.580
It is Friday.

37:21.830 --> 37:24.790
Well, you know what Jon
used to say about pizza night.

37:24.790 --> 37:27.880
Everyone's invited.

37:27.880 --> 37:36.420
♪♪

37:36.420 --> 37:37.920
Yes!

37:39.460 --> 37:42.080
Is this what
we're doing now? Hmm?

37:42.080 --> 37:44.170
Just being big people?

37:44.170 --> 37:47.290
Yeah.
Maybe you should try it.

37:47.290 --> 37:53.920
♪♪

37:53.920 --> 37:55.500
I'm gonna --
I'm right behind you.

37:55.500 --> 37:56.580
Yeah.

37:56.580 --> 38:02.290
♪♪

38:02.290 --> 38:04.500
How you doing?

38:04.500 --> 38:06.620
That depends.

38:06.620 --> 38:07.830
How we doing?

38:07.830 --> 38:09.080
We've been better.

38:11.960 --> 38:14.460
But we're gonna try
and get back there.

38:14.460 --> 38:20.920
♪♪

38:20.920 --> 38:22.710
[ Indistinct conversations ]

38:22.710 --> 38:25.080
[ Door closes ]

38:25.080 --> 38:28.120
Hi, Maggie.
Hey, Sophie.

38:28.120 --> 38:30.210
Hey.
Hey.

38:30.210 --> 38:34.920
Um...I just want to say that
I know it can't be easy,

38:34.920 --> 38:37.750
but I'm glad you're here.

38:37.750 --> 38:40.000
Yeah, thanks.

38:40.000 --> 38:45.290
And I didn't realize
with you and Eddie...

38:45.290 --> 38:46.960
Look, I didn't realize
everything that was going on,

38:46.960 --> 38:50.080
and I'm sorry
I wasn't there for you.

38:51.920 --> 38:55.170
♪♪

38:55.170 --> 38:56.960
What?

38:56.960 --> 39:01.250
It's just, even now, after
everything that's happened,

39:01.250 --> 39:04.920
Jon's still finding a way
to make me feel welcome.

39:08.620 --> 39:11.080
Ooh.

39:11.080 --> 39:12.960
You get a Shasta.

39:12.960 --> 39:15.250
And you get a Shasta.

39:15.250 --> 39:19.080
And you get a Shasta!
Whoa!

39:19.080 --> 39:21.290
Enjoy 'em, people,
because I quit my job!

39:21.290 --> 39:23.080
-What?
-What?

39:23.080 --> 39:25.210
-Yeah.
-What is this?

39:25.210 --> 39:26.710
Okay, so what does
this mean?

39:26.710 --> 39:29.880
This means that,
no matter what it takes,

39:29.880 --> 39:31.250
I'm gonna make my movie.

39:31.250 --> 39:32.750
-Oh, yes. Yes!
-[ Laughs ] I know!

39:32.750 --> 39:33.790
Gary: What?

39:33.790 --> 39:35.380
Thank you.
Thank you.

39:35.380 --> 39:38.210
And what, pray tell,
inspired this move?

39:38.210 --> 39:40.120
A very special woman
in my life.

39:40.120 --> 39:42.250
[ Glass clinks ]

39:42.250 --> 39:44.120
All right.

39:44.120 --> 39:46.380
You guys can start seeing
each other.

39:46.380 --> 39:47.670
Thank you.

39:47.670 --> 39:51.500
